# Netlify reads this file automatically at deploy time and applies these
# headers to every response. If you're hosting elsewhere (Vercel, Cloudflare
# Pages, GitHub Pages + a CDN, etc.), your host will have its own equivalent
# config format — the three headers below are what matter, wherever they end
# up configured. See SECURITY.md (OWASP A05) for why each one is here.

/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
